Implement `chipper new <name>`.

Behavior:
- Create a new ticket file in the tickets directory with the given name
- Open $EDITOR for content entry if set; otherwise read multi-line stdin until Ctrl+D
- Once content is saved, prompt for a slug (suggested from filename) and register it in chipper-slugs
- Immediately run the interactive sort to place the ticket in chipper-queue
- Reject slug if it conflicts with an existing slug

Depends on: cli-scaffolding, manifest-implementation, sort-command

